 and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual medieval vernacular form of   Margaret   (now also commonly spelled   Marjorie  ). This form of the name is preserved in the nursery rhyme ‘See-saw, Margery Daw’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":6,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Margery Leigh was born in 1376, in Radnor, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Thomas de Legh of Booths Hall, was 32 and her mother, Anna (or Jane) Leigh, was 32. She married Thomas De Wilbraham in 1389. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1430, in Cheshire, England, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1376–1430":"1376–1430","1377–Female":"1377–Surnud","1380–1422":"1380–1422","1372–1409":"1372–1409","1391–1467":"1391–1467","1403–1446":"1403–1446","1345–1404":"1345–1404","1345–Female":"1345–Surnud","10 December 1409":"10. detsember 1409","20 July 1404":"20. juuli 1404","1372":"1372","1382":"1382","1391":"1391","1380":"1380","1404":"1404","1403":"1403","1446":"1446","1467":"1467","1389":"1389","1345":"1345","1422":"1422","1377":"1377","1376":"1376","1430":"1430","1409":"1409","about 1363":"umbes 1363","Addington, Surrey, England, United Kingdom":"Addington, Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warton, Lancashire, England":"Warton, Lancashire, England","Radnor, Cheshire, England":"Radnor, Cheshire, England","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, England","Radnor Woodhey, Cheshire, England":"Radnor, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1376–1430"